comments.text: I Found a loophole to the "one, you're terminated, you can't make anymore channels" rule. If you make a channel for the first time, and then you make a second channel under a different email address while your first channel is up, and your first channel is terminated, you still have your second channel, because it's under a different email address, and technically, it's not against the Youtube TOS. Also, just because there's a rule that disallows you from making a new youtube account if yours gets terminated, doesn't mean it's actually enforced
